" ============================================================================
" .ideameowrc — THE default keymap of the ideameow plugin
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" Like meow in Emacs, the plugin binds no keys in code: this file defines
" every default — the NORMAL/MOTION layout and the whole SPC keypad table —
" and ships bundled inside the plugin jar. A ~/.ideameowrc in your home
" directory (Linux/macOS: ~/.ideameowrc, Windows: C:\Users\<you>\.ideameowrc)
" overrides it entry by entry — only the lines you change matter; a deleted
" line falls back to the bundled default (bind `ignore` to disable a key).
" Open it with SPC c m — the first press creates ~/.ideameowrc as a full
" copy of this file; reload after editing with SPC c M ("Reload .ideameowrc").
"
" Syntax (see the README for the full guide):
"   nmap <key> <action>(ActionId)     NORMAL-mode key -> IDE action
"   nmap <key> <meow-command>         NORMAL-mode key -> named meow command
"   nmap <key> <meow keys>            NORMAL-mode key -> replayed meow keys
"   nnoremap ...                      like nmap, but the RHS resolves through
"                                     these bundled defaults, skipping user maps
"   mmap / mnoremap <key> <target>    the same, for MOTION mode (the keymap
"                                     of tool-window trees; read-only
"                                     editors stay NORMAL)
"   map <leader><seq> <target>        keypad (SPC) entry
"   desc <leader><seq> <text>         which-key label for an entry or a group
"   set timeoutlen=300                which-key popup delay in ms
"   set nowhich-key                   turn the which-key popup off
"
" Ported from intellij-community-settings/ideavim/.ideavimrc. Not portable
" (and why) is listed at the bottom. The meow layout itself needs NO porting —
" the plugin implements it natively; the layout section right below IS the
" keymap (like meow-normal-define-key in Emacs), so any key can be rebound.
" Within this file, a later line for the same key wins.
" ============================================================================

set which-key
set timeoutlen=300

" ============================================================================
" The meow layout — QWERTY by default, every key rebindable
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" These lines ARE the default layout (there is no key table in the plugin's
" code). Rebind any key to another meow command, to an <action>(...), or to
" replayed keys; bind a key to `ignore` to disable it. In a home ~/.ideameowrc
" only overrides are needed — a key without a home line keeps its binding
" from this bundled file. mmap does the same for MOTION mode.
" SPC is the keypad key and cannot be remapped; ESC and modifier
" chords never reach the modal engine (put those on the IDE keymap).
" ============================================================================

" expand / counts
nmap 0 meow-expand-0
nmap 1 meow-expand-1
nmap 2 meow-expand-2
nmap 3 meow-expand-3
nmap 4 meow-expand-4
nmap 5 meow-expand-5
nmap 6 meow-expand-6
nmap 7 meow-expand-7
nmap 8 meow-expand-8
nmap 9 meow-expand-9
nmap - meow-negative-argument

" selections / things
nmap ; meow-reverse
nmap , meow-inner-of-thing
nmap . meow-bounds-of-thing
nmap [ meow-beginning-of-thing
nmap ] meow-end-of-thing
nmap < meow-beginning-of-thing
nmap > meow-end-of-thing

" the letter keys
nmap a meow-append
nmap A meow-open-below
nmap b meow-back-word
nmap B meow-back-symbol
nmap c meow-change
nmap d meow-delete
nmap D meow-backward-delete
nmap e meow-next-word
nmap E meow-next-symbol
nmap f meow-find
nmap g meow-cancel-selection
nmap G meow-grab
nmap h meow-left
nmap H meow-left-expand
nmap i meow-insert
nmap I meow-open-above
nmap j meow-next
nmap J meow-next-expand
nmap k meow-prev
nmap K meow-prev-expand
nmap l meow-right
nmap L meow-right-expand
nmap m meow-join
nmap n meow-search
nmap o meow-block
nmap O meow-to-block
nmap p meow-yank
nmap q meow-quit
nmap Q meow-goto-line
nmap r meow-replace
nmap R meow-swap-grab
nmap s meow-kill
nmap t meow-till
nmap u meow-undo
nmap U meow-undo-in-selection
nmap v meow-visit
nmap w meow-mark-word
nmap W meow-mark-symbol
nmap x meow-line
nmap X meow-goto-line
nmap y meow-save
nmap Y meow-sync-grab
nmap z meow-pop-selection
nmap ' repeat

" MOTION mode — meow's reduced state for special contexts, exactly like
" special buffers in Emacs. Read-only editors do NOT use it (they stay
" NORMAL, like Emacs read-only buffers, with the modify commands inert);
" it IS the keymap of tool-window trees — project view, structure, TODO,
" find results, ... — where j/k/h/l move like the arrow keys (h collapses
" or goes to the parent, l expands or enters), q hides the tool window,
" and every unmapped key keeps its native meaning: Enter opens, any other
" letter still starts speed search. Add your own the same way, e.g.
"   mmap o <action>(EditSource)            open without leaving the tree
"   mmap r <action>(SynchronizeCurrentFile) NERDTree-style refresh
" and `mmap <key> ignore` gives a key back to the tree (native speed
" search) — on trees ignore means don't intercept, not swallow.
mmap j meow-next
mmap k meow-prev
mmap h meow-left
mmap l meow-right
mmap q <action>(HideActiveWindow)

" ============================================================================
" The keypad (SPC) table — every entry an rc line, like the layout above
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" In Emacs, SPC x / c / m reach the C-x / C-c / M- keymaps; here the same
" sequences dispatch IDE actions, mirroring the companion .ideavimrc leader
" scheme. SPC 0-9 (digit argument), SPC ? (cheatsheet) and SPC / (describe
" key) are reserved by the keypad itself and cannot be remapped.
" Finding an action's id for <action>(...): SPC i d toggles action-id
" tracking (IdeaVim's "Track Action IDs") — while it is on, every action you
" perform shows a balloon with its id and a Copy Action Id button.
" ============================================================================

map <leader>bb <action>(RecentFiles)
map <leader>bm <action>(ToggleBookmark)
map <leader>bj <action>(ShowBookmarks)
map <leader>b0 <action>(ToggleBookmark0)
map <leader>b1 <action>(ToggleBookmark1)
map <leader>b2 <action>(ToggleBookmark2)
map <leader>b3 <action>(ToggleBookmark3)
map <leader>b4 <action>(ToggleBookmark4)
map <leader>b5 <action>(ToggleBookmark5)
map <leader>b6 <action>(ToggleBookmark6)
map <leader>b7 <action>(ToggleBookmark7)
map <leader>b8 <action>(ToggleBookmark8)
map <leader>b9 <action>(ToggleBookmark9)
map <leader><Space> <action>(Switcher)

" SPC x = C-x: files / buffers / windows
map <leader>xf <action>(GotoFile)
map <leader>xs <action>(SaveAll)
map <leader>xb <action>(RecentFiles)
map <leader>xk <action>(CloseContent)
map <leader>xd <action>(ActivateProjectToolWindow)
map <leader>xg <action>(ActivateVersionControlToolWindow)
map <leader>xo <action>(NextSplitter)
map <leader>xu <action>(LocalHistory.ShowHistory)
map <leader>xv <action>(Vcs.Operations.Popup)
map <leader>xc <action>(CloseProject)
map <leader>x0 <action>(Unsplit)
map <leader>x1 <action>(UnsplitAll)
map <leader>x2 <action>(SplitHorizontally)
map <leader>x3 <action>(SplitVertically)

" SPC x p = C-x p: project.el
map <leader>xpf <action>(GotoFile)
map <leader>xpb <action>(RecentFiles)
map <leader>xpg <action>(FindInPath)
map <leader>xpr <action>(ReplaceInPath)
map <leader>xpc <action>(CompileProject)

" SPC x r = C-x r: bookmarks (init.el: C-x r b = consult-bookmark)
map <leader>xrb <action>(ShowBookmarks)

" SPC c = C-c: personal commands
map <leader>cf <action>(GotoFile)
map <leader>cs <action>(SaveAll)
map <leader>ck <action>(CloseContent)
map <leader>cr <action>(FindInPath)
map <leader>ce <action>(EditorSelectWord)
map <leader>ca <action>(ActivateTODOToolWindow)
map <leader>cc <action>(NewScratchFile)
map <leader>cl <action>(CopyReference)
map <leader>cg <action>(Vcs.Operations.Popup)

" SPC c m / M: edit / reload ~/.ideameowrc
map <leader>cm <action>(Ideameow.EditRc)
map <leader>cM <action>(Ideameow.ReloadRc)

" SPC c j: avy jumps — implemented natively by the plugin, no AceJump needed
map <leader>cjw avy-goto-char-timer
map <leader>cjc avy-goto-char-timer
map <leader>cjl avy-goto-line

" SPC m = M-: meta
map <leader>mx <action>(GotoAction)
map <leader>mo avy-goto-char-timer
map <leader>mr <action>(EditorSelectWord)
map <leader>mR <action>(EditorUnSelectWord)
map <leader>my <action>(PasteMultiple)
map <leader>m. <action>(GotoDeclaration)
map <leader>mg avy-goto-line
map <leader>msr <action>(FindInPath)
map <leader>msl <action>(Find)
map <leader>mss <action>(Find)
map <leader>msL <action>(FindInPath)
map <leader>mso <action>(FileStructurePopup)

" SPC w: the window map (Emacs C-c w)
map <leader>wv <action>(SplitVertically)
map <leader>ws <action>(SplitHorizontally)
map <leader>wd <action>(Unsplit)
map <leader>wD <action>(UnsplitAll)
map <leader>wm <action>(UnsplitAll)
map <leader>ww <action>(NextSplitter)
map <leader>wW <action>(MoveEditorToOppositeTabGroup)
" h/j/k/l: windmove, ported from init.el — directional focus over editor
" splits AND diff panes, from the caret like Emacs. The plugin also binds
" plain Shift+arrows to these, i.e. (windmove-default-keybindings) — that
" lives on the IDE keymap (Settings > Keymap > Windmove *), not in this rc,
" because modifier chords never reach the modal engine.
map <leader>wh <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveLeft)
map <leader>wj <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveDown)
map <leader>wk <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveUp)
map <leader>wl <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveRight)
" H/J/K/L: windmove-swap-states — the capitals mirror the h/j/k/l moves:
" your file and the focus travel to the neighbouring split, its file comes
" back to yours (editor splits only; a diff pane can't be swapped)
map <leader>wH <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveSwapLeft)
map <leader>wJ <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveSwapDown)
map <leader>wK <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveSwapUp)
map <leader>wL <action>(Ideameow.WindmoveSwapRight)
map <leader>wi <action>(EditorIncreaseFontSize)
map <leader>w= <action>(EditorIncreaseFontSize)
map <leader>wo <action>(EditorDecreaseFontSize)
map <leader>w- <action>(EditorDecreaseFontSize)
map <leader>wu <action>(EditorResetFontSize)
map <leader>w0 <action>(EditorResetFontSize)

" --- avy jumps, mirroring init.el (native port of avy 0.5.0 — no plugin) ----
" init.el: S = avy-goto-char-timer, Q = avy-goto-line. X still goes-to-line,
" so overriding Q costs nothing. Type chars (0.25 s pause labels the
" matches), then hit a label key; Q labels visible lines, digits switch to
" a line-number prompt.
nmap S avy-goto-char-timer
nmap Q avy-goto-line

" --- split resizing (ideavimrc: - = _ +) ------------------------------------
" '-' stays meow's negative-argument (the reason ideavimrc used '-' here was
" that vim lacks negative counts — this plugin doesn't). The other three keys
" are free in the meow layout:
nmap = <action>(StretchSplitToTop)
nmap _ <action>(StretchSplitToLeft)
nmap + <action>(StretchSplitToRight)

" --- which-key labels for the keypad groups above ----------------------------
desc <leader>b bookmark (m set / 0-9 slots / j jump) · b buffers
desc <leader>x C-x · file / buffer / window
desc <leader>xp C-x p · project
desc <leader>xr C-x r · bookmarks
desc <leader>c C-c · commands (= M-m)
desc <leader>cj C-c j · avy jump
desc <leader>m M- · meta
desc <leader>ms M-s · search
desc <leader>w window map (Emacs C-c w)

