" --- SPC ] / SPC [ — next / prev navigation ------------------------------------------------------
" ideavimrc used ]c [c ]d [d ]e [e in NORMAL; multi-key NORMAL sequences don't
" exist here ([ ] are meow's beginning/end-of-thing), so they live on the
" keypad instead.
desc <leader>. next (change / diff / error)
map <leader>.c <action>(VcsShowNextChangeMarker)
map <leader>.d <action>(NextDiff)
map <leader>.e <action>(GotoNextError)
desc <leader>, previous (change / diff / error)
map <leader>,c <action>(VcsShowPrevChangeMarker)
map <leader>,d <action>(PreviousDiff)
map <leader>,e <action>(GotoPreviousError)

" ============================================================================
" Repeat groups — Emacs repeat-mode, ported (init.el's transient repeat maps)
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" After any binding whose TARGET is listed in a group below — membership is
" the target, not the key, like the repeat-map property on an Emacs command —
" the next keypress is first looked up in that group: a member key
" re-dispatches its target and keeps the run alive; any other key (or ESC)
" ends the run and keeps its normal meaning (Emacs transient-keymap
" fall-through — nothing is swallowed, and there is no timeout). The entering
" keypad key needn't be a member: init.el sets repeat-check-key 'no for the
" same reason. Syntax:
"   repeat <group> <key> <target>     target grammar = the map-line RHS
"   repeat <group> <key> ignore       give a bundled group's key back
" Ported 1:1 from init.el: flymake -> error, diff-hl -> change, text-scale ->
" zoom, expreg -> expand (winner-mode has no analog — no layout history).
" So: SPC . e then . . , walks errors; SPC w i then i i i keeps zooming.
repeat error . <action>(GotoNextError)
repeat error , <action>(GotoPreviousError)
repeat change . <action>(VcsShowNextChangeMarker)
repeat change , <action>(VcsShowPrevChangeMarker)
repeat zoom i <action>(EditorIncreaseFontSize)
repeat zoom = <action>(EditorIncreaseFontSize)
repeat zoom o <action>(EditorDecreaseFontSize)
repeat zoom - <action>(EditorDecreaseFontSize)
repeat zoom u <action>(EditorResetFontSize)
repeat zoom 0 <action>(EditorResetFontSize)
repeat expand . <action>(EditorSelectWord)
repeat expand , <action>(EditorUnSelectWord)
" not a default group (init.el has none for diffs) — add your own like:
"   repeat diff . <action>(NextDiff)
"   repeat diff , <action>(PreviousDiff)

" ============================================================================
" NOT ported from .ideavimrc, and why
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" * the whole meow-emulation section (w e b x s d c y r H-L, digits, , . < >,
"   G/R/Y, m, z, ') — the plugin implements real meow; nothing to emulate.
"   The layout block at the top of this file is the native keymap itself.
" * set clipboard/ideajoin/number/relativenumber/sethandler — IdeaVim/vim
"   options; the IDE and the plugin handle these themselves. Any such lines
"   are ignored if pasted, so copying your .ideavimrc wholesale is safe.
" * <A-m> leader alias, C-key routing — only printable keys reach the meow
"   engine; use the IDE keymap for modifier chords.
" * SPC / (comment) and SPC ? — reserved by the keypad for describe-key and
"   the cheatsheet. Comment-line is on the IDE's usual Ctrl-/ chord.
" * :tabm / :delmarks / :set number! ex-commands — no ex layer here.
" * SPC <CR> (intentions): Enter can't be a keypad key; use Alt-Enter or
"   SPC s I (ShowIntentionActions).
" ============================================================================
